# Azure resource group
In this course, we are going to use the **wisdompetmedicine** resource group to deploy the required Azure services, such as Azure Service Bus and Azure Cosmos DB.

## Task 1: Navigate to the Azure Portal
1. By using a web browser, navigate to https://portal.azure.com

## Task 2: Create the wisdompetmedicine resource group
1. In the Azure Portal home page, select Resource groups
2. In the **Resource groups** page, select the Create button 
3. In the Create a resource group page, set the following properties:
    - Resource group name: **wisdompetmedicine**
    - Region: Select the region that is closest to your current location
4. Select **Review + create**

# Azure Service Bus
In this course, we are going to use Azure Service Bus as the message broker for asynchronous communication.  You can take the following steps to deploy it in your Azure subscription.

## Task 1: Navigate to the Azure Portal
1. By using a web browser, navigate to https://portal.azure.com.

## Task 2: Create the Azure Service Bus service
1. In the Azure Portal home page, select **Create a resource**.

2. Type **Service Bus** in the search text box.  Select **Service Bus** from the drop-down list.

    ![](images/createresource-servicebus.jpg)


3. Select **Create**.

    ![](images/create-servicebus.jpg)
    
4. In the Create namespace page, set the following values:
    - Resource group: **wisdompetmedicine**.
    - Namespace name: **wisdompetmedicine**.
    - Location: Select the region that is closest to your current location.
    - Pricing tier: Select **Standard**.
    > Note: The Standard tier is required, since we are going to use the Topics component of Azure Service Bus.
    
5. Select **Review + create** and then select **Create**.

    ![][image_ref_9iuhvtn8]


## Task 3: Create the topics

1. In the **Overview** page of the **wisdompetmedicine** Service Bus Namespace blade, select **+Topic**.
    
    ![][image_ref_gfjby1fe]

2. In the Create topic blade, set the topic name as **pet-flagged-for-adoption**.

3. Select **Create**.
    
    ![][image_ref_uui9h078]


4. Repeat steps 1-3 for the **pet-transferred-to-hospital** topic.

## Task 4: Create the subscriptions
1. In the **Topics** page of the **wisdompetmedicine** Service Bus Namespace blade, you should see both topics that you have just created.  

    ![][image_ref_eq9fc7yb]

2. Select the **pet-flagged-for-adoption** topic.

3. In the **pet-flagged-for-adoption** topic blade, select **+Subscription**

    ![][image_ref_tsyddkah]


4. Set the following values:
    - Name: **pet-flagged-for-adoption**.
    - Max delivery count: **10**.

5. Select **Create**.

    ![][image_ref_18f2m0ea]


6. Repeat steps 2-5 for the **pet-transferred-to-hospital** topic.  Use its same name for the subscription name, and also use a max delivery count of 10.

## Task 5: Get the Service Bus connection string
1. In the **Shared access policies** page of the **wisdompetmedicine** Service Bus Namespace blade, select **RootManageSharedAccessKey**.

2. Copy the primary connection string by selecting the copy button.

    ![][image_ref_1d29t1e8]

3. Paste the connection string in a Notepad or any other text editing tool, since you are going to use it in the course.


At this point, your Azure Service Bus is ready to be used in the course.

# Azure Cosmos DB
In this course, we are going to use Azure Cosmos DB to store the events from the Hospital domain model.  You can take the following steps to deploy it in your Azure subscription.

## Task 1: Navigate to the Azure Portal
1. By using a web browser, navigate to https://portal.azure.com.

## Task 2: Create the Azure Cosmos DB account
1. In the Azure Portal home page, select **Create a resource**.

2. Select Azure Cosmos DB from the list.

    ![][image_ref_u6xtx64d]

3. In the **Select API option** blade, select the **Create** button of the **Core (SQL) - Recommended** option.

    ![][image_ref_b30b3ona]
    
4. Set the following values:
    - Resource group: **wisdompetmedicine**.
    - Account Name: **wisdompetmedicine**.
    - Location: Select the region that is closest to your current location.
    - Capacity mode: **Serverless**

5. Select **Review + create**, then select **Create**.

    ![][image_ref_3506qyv8]
    
## Task 3: Create database and container

1. In the Data Explorer page of the **wisdompetmedicine** Azure Cosmos DB account blade, select Data Explorer.

2. Select **New Container**.

3. In the New Container blade, set the following values:
    - Database Id - Create new: **WisdomPetMedicine**.
    - Container Id: **Patients**.
    - Partition key: **/aggregateId**.
    
4. Select **OK**

    ![](images/azurecosmosdb-newcontainer.png)

## Task 4: Get connection string
1. In the **Keys** page of the **wisdompetmedicine** Azure Cosmos DB account blade, copy the primary connection string by selecting the copy button.

    ![](images/azurecosmosdb-getconnectionstring.jpg)
    
2. Paste the connection string in a Notepad or any other text editing tool, since you are going to use it in the course.


At this point, your Azure Cosmos DB account is ready to be used in the course.
